thread.title: Joey Logano corn maze recreates Daytona 500 celebration
thread.title_full: Joey Logano corn maze recreates Daytona 500 celebration

author: Josh Richter - Shake and Bake Crew
title: Joey Logano corn maze recreates Daytona 500 celebration
text:
Joey Logano corn maze recreates Daytona 500 celebration FOXSports 1 day ago Josh Richter - Shake and Bake Crew Â© Getty Images DOVER, DE - OCTOBER 02: Joey Logano, driver of the #22 Shell/Pennzoil Ford, speaks to the media before practice for the NASCAR Sprint Cup Series AAA 400 at Dover International Speedway on October 2, 2015 in Dover, Delaware. A corn maze of his likeness was created at a farm in Arizona. (Photo by Brian Lawdermilk/Getty Images) Nothing goes together quite like "Sliced Bread" and corn.
AdChoices Joey Logano received a surprise at Dover when he found out that a corn maze has been created in his honor at Schnepf Farms in Queen Creek, Arizona. Logano's post-Daytona 500 celebration was used as inspiration.
That's pretty close. There are two other corn mazes next to Logano's - one in the shape of the Shell logo and the other promoting 811, the national call before you dig phone number.
"I was blown away by what I saw," said Logano. "The maze is incredible and I have never seen anything like before, nor would I have ever imagined being a part of something like this when I started racing. I think it's very cool that it is symbolic of our Daytona 500 win. That was a pretty big surprise and something I'll always remember. I'm pretty sure I'd get lost inside that thing."
